  "prompt": "What has been the Industrialization of India since its independence?",
  "response": "Since India's independence in 1947, the country has undergone significant industrialization through several key phases:\n\n1. Initial Phase (1950-1970):\n- Planned economy under socialist model\n- Focus on heavy industries and public sector\n- Government-led industrial development\n- Establishment of large public sector enterprises\n- Import substitution strategy\n\n2. License Raj Period (1960-1980):\n- Strict government control over industrial growth\n- Complex bureaucratic regulations\n- Limited private sector participation\n- Slow industrial expansion\n\n3. Liberalization Phase (1991 onwards):\n- Economic reforms introduced\n- Dismantling of license raj\n- Opening up of economy\n- Encouraging foreign direct investment\n- Privatization of public sector enterprises\n\n4. Modern Industrialization Characteristics:\n- Emergence of manufacturing and service sectors\n- Growth of information technology\n- Automotive and pharmaceutical industries\n- Development of special economic zones\n- Increased global competitiveness\n\n5. Key Industrial Sectors:\n- Information Technology\n- Automotive manufacturing\n- Pharmaceuticals\n- Textiles\n- Steel and metal manufacturing\n- Chemical industries\n- Electronics\n\n6. Recent Developments:\n- \"Make in India\" initiative\n- Increased focus on manufacturing\n- Digital transformation\n- Startup ecosystem growth\n\nThe industrialization journey has transformed India from an agrarian economy to a diverse, technology-driven industrial nation.",
